    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>coconut flakes</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and golden</p><p>Once toasted, set aside until serving and reserve the pan \u2013 these are your <strong>toasted coconut flakes</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-sambal-mussels-with-sticky-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-sambal-mussels-with-sticky-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans </strong>in half</p><p>Roll your <strong>lime[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-sambal-mussels-with-sticky-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-sambal-mussels-with-sticky-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once beginning to soften, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> to the pan with your <strong>ginger paste</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-sambal-mussels-with-sticky-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>mussels</strong> and any juices to the pan with the <strong>halved green beans</strong>, your <strong>tamarind paste</strong>, a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and cook for 5-6 min or until the mussels are cooked through and the green beans are tender with a slight bite</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 pans!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-sambal-mussels-with-sticky-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mussels are cooked, add your <strong>sambal </strong>and a squeeze of <strong>lime juice</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 these are your <strong>sambal mussels</strong></p><p>Cut the remaining <strong>lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Tip: Discard any mussels which shells have not opened!</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/coconut-sambal-mussels-with-sticky-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sambal mussels </strong>with the <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>in the centre</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Garnish the rice with the <strong>toasted coconut flakes</strong> and a <strong>lime wedge</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
